Title: LaserScope An atmospheric monitoring system for nitrogen fluorescence cosmic ray detectors.  
Author: David J. Bird 
Address: Adelaide S.A., 5005, Australia  
Affiliation: Department of Physics and Mathematical Physics University of  
Abstract: The analysis of cosmic ray data from nitrogen fluorescence detectors requires knowledge of the atmospheric absorption and scattering profile. This is best measured in situ. A new device constructed for probing the atmosphere, based upon readily available commercial equipment and remotely controllable, is discussed below. Preliminary results from tests with the High Resolution Flys Eye Detector are also presented. 
